# Equality Analysis (Excel)

## Overview

In this project, I worked with employee compensation data to understand how fair the distribution is across different factories and job roles. The goal was to turn raw scores into clear and meaningful categories.

## What I Did

* Explored the dataset to understand its structure
* Created a new column called **Equality Class**
* Used Excel functions (IFS, AND, OR) to classify each value into:

  * Fair
  * Unfair
  * Highly Discriminative
* Converted raw numerical values into easy-to-understand categories

## Tools Used

* Microsoft Excel (IFS, AND, OR, basic data analysis)

## Key Insights

* Identified areas with fair and unfair compensation
* Highlighted highly discriminative cases
* Made the dataset easier to interpret at a glance

